A FUEL-efficient home for the future is opening its doors to the public next weekend. Take a look inside the 'green' house A FUEL-efficient home for the future is opening its doors to the public next weekend.Built at Ravenscraig, in Motherwell, the &quot;green&quot; house, which even boasts kitchen surfaces made from recycled coffee cups, is open to businesses on Friday and families on Saturday.The Green Network event is organised by the Energy Saving Trust and Resource Efficient Scotland. 